history.content: For 16B, major no longer matters. If the lecture has seats, and there are sections with seats, drop the course and re-add with different section

Hello all,

I'm in the CoE attempting to transfer to EECS and I'm waitlisted for these classes:

EE16B waitlist position 38

CS61B waitlist position 142

The lab section for EE16B and the discussion section for CS61B are both full.  At this point, would it be worth it for me to be put to the back of the waitlist and re-enroll in a different lab/discussion section?  Or would it be better for me to stay in these classes and hope that people drop out?

Many thanks and good luck to you all on finals.
